    Overview

    Authentication

    Envysion RQ Data Connect supports many different methods of authentication, see Authentication Options.

    Endpoints

    • Sandbox: https://rqdataconnectdemo.iqmetrix.net
    • Production: https://rqdataconnect.iqmetrix.net

    Getting Partner Relationships

    Request

    GET /partner/relationships?Auth={Auth}&Response={Response}

    Headers

    • Authorization: Bearer (Access Token) (Optional) - Bearer token used for authentication. For other methods of authentication, see Authentication Options
    • Accept-Encoding: gzip (Optional) - Compression algorithm. For other methods of compression, see Compression Options

    URI Parameters

    • Auth (Optional) - Basic token used for authentication. For other methods of authentication, see Authentication Options
    • Response (Optional) - Default is JSON. For other methods of response, see Response Options
    Example
    • HTTP
    • cURL
    • C# (RestSharp)
    • Java (HttpComponents)
    • Ruby (rest-client)
    GET /partner/relationships

    curl -X GET "https://rqdataconnectdemo.iqmetrix.net/partner/relationships"
    This code sample uses RestSharp, ensure you install the nuget package and include Using RestSharp; at the top of your file. 
    static IRestResponse GettingPartnerRelationships()
{
    var client = new RestClient("https://rqdataconnectdemo.iqmetrix.net/partner/relationships");
    var request = new RestRequest(Method.GET);
     

    

    return client.Execute(request);
}
    This code sample uses Apache HttpComponents, ensure you download and include the required Jars. 
    
import org.apache.http.client.methods.CloseableHttpResponse;
import org.apache.http.client.methods.HttpGet;
import org.apache.http.impl.client.CloseableHttpClient;
import org.apache.http.impl.client.HttpClients;
import java.io.IOException;

public static CloseableHttpResponse GettingPartnerRelationships() throws IOException {
    CloseableHttpClient httpClient = HttpClients.createDefault();
    HttpGet request = new HttpGet("https://rqdataconnectdemo.iqmetrix.net/partner/relationships");
     
    
    return httpClient.execute(request);
}
    This code sample uses rest-client, ensure you gem install rest-client. 
    require 'rest-client'

    }

    URI Parameters

    • CompanyId (Required) - Identifier for a Company
    • Auth (Optional) - Basic token used for authentication. For other methods of authentication, see Authentication Options
    • Response (Optional) - Default is JSON. For other methods of response, see Response Options
